                            <p class="text-justify">Lufthansa is not just a fine airline for the travel of German but also a good option to fly for the United States, Europe, and Asia. Counted in the list of the world’s largest airlines, there is no need to introduce the name of this airline. Baggage is an important concern for the flyers when they consider the Lufthansa Airlines Booking. The blog tells, you about the outright review of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/lufthansa-airlines.aspx">Lufthansa Airlines Baggage Policy</a> that you should not miss at all. </p>
                            <h2>What Information You Can Grab from Lufthansa Baggage Policy?</h2>
                            <p class="text-justify">1). Carry-On Baggage</p>
                            <p class="text-justify">2). Free Baggage Policy</p>
                            <p class="text-justify">3). Special Baggage</p>
                            <h2>1). Lufthansa Also Provide Free Baggage Calculator:</h2>
                            <p class="text-justify">Are you confused about the baggage allowance with the upcoming Lufthansa Reservations? Had you checked the tool Lufthansa Baggage Calculator? Yes, by using this astonishing calculator in few steps you can know about the baggage charges and information for your route, fare, and travel class. Using the baggage calculator is totally flexible for the flyers. They just have to need to put the travel information in the tool and the current baggage, terms, policies, free baggage, carry-on and checked baggage will display on their screen. Don’t miss the use of this tool before pack your bags for Lufthansa Flights. </p>
                            <h2>2). Lufthansa Airlines Free Baggage Rules: </h2>
                            <p class="text-justify">Every airline provides free baggage access to the flyers for the travel goals. However, for the free baggage, they are also required to follow the rules of size, quantity, and weight. In this tab, we are going to disclose the free baggage policy of Lufthansa Airlines. We listed the information of particular routes about the free baggage of the airline. </p>
                            <h3>2.1). Add Name and Phone Number with Tag on Your Bag: </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">Always take care about the phone number and name on each bag when you fly with Lufthansa Airlines before checking at the airport. This will reduce the chances of missing luggage for your journey. If you had not done this at the home, then this facility is also available at the airport check-in counter where you can get the bag tags, stickers for your baggage to identify your bag after departure. Passengers can also use their bag tags in Lufthansa Airlines. </p>
                            <h3>2.2). What is Bag Drop-Off Deadlines or Check-In Deadlines in Lufthansa Air? </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">Passengers can also view the data and information about the check-in options at the airport. Check-in deadlines or bag drop-off deadlines are mainly related to the flight's departure time or flights is on time. You should not cross this deadline and always print the boarding pass before the bag drop-off deadlines; otherwise, you may also miss your flight. On the other hand, if you complete this process via the online check-in of Lufthansa or Mobile App Check-In at Lufthansa then you must complete the checked baggage process as well. </p>
                            <h4>A). How to find the check-in deadlines of Lufthansa Airlines? </h4>
                            <p class="text-justify"><a href="https://www.lufthansa.com/us/en/check-in-deadlines">Click Here </a>to find the Check-In Deadlines of the airlines. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">Otherwise, you can also visit the Lufthansa Airlines Reservations Official Site to view the deadlines of check-in. Once you click on the link then fill in the information about “Flight Details” and then select “Display check-in information". After this process is complete, then you can explore the Lufthansa Airlines Bag Drop-Off Deadlines for your particular travel class and airport on the page. </p>
                            <h4>B). How Lufthansa Airlines Use Passengers Data and Baggage Data? </h4>
                            <p class="text-justify">One more question that came to the mind of flyers is about the data collected by the airlines regarding the baggage. How do the airlines use this data? Don’t worry about this situation as well because the airline collects this data for the onward transportation of passenger’s baggage safely and timely. The data is also used to support the German Customs Authorities in the accomplishment of their legal duties. </p>
                            <h3>2.3). Lufthansa Airlines Carry-On Baggage Size Required: </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">The maximum size per piece of baggage as per the Lufthansa Air Baggage Policy is 158 cm (width X + height Y + depth Z). If your carry-on item is larger then it will be counted as excess baggage. </p>
                            <h3>2.4). Free Baggage Detail on the Europe Flights for Travel Class: </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">Weight and the number of free baggage allowed in the Lufthansa Airlines Flights are vital to know for the passengers. Here is the overview on this concern: </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">1). For the economy class, 1 item of carry-on baggage is allowed up to 8 KG</p>
                            <p class="text-justify">2). For the Economy Classic and Flex, 1 item of carry-on baggage is allowed up to 8 KG and 1 Item of Baggage Up to 23 KG is allowed. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">3). For the business class, 2 items of carry-on baggage are allowed, each up to 8 KG, and 2 Items of checked baggage are allowed, each up to 32 KG. </p>
                            <h3>2.5). Free Baggage Detail for Intercontinental Flights According to the Travel Class: </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">Traveling for the Intercontinental flights and still not aware of the free baggage detail of the airline means you should check the baggage allowance in Lufthansa Airlines as per your travel class. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">1). If you fly in the economy light then only 1 carry-on item is allowed up to 8 KG</p>
                            <p class="text-justify">2). Flying in the economy class, means something is more for you in the baggage and 1 item of carry-on baggage up to 8 KG is allowed and 1 item of baggage up to 23 KG is allowed. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">3). Premium economy class is also the travel class accessible on the Lufthansa Airlines Intercontinental flights for the passengers. In this fare class, 1 item of carry-on baggage up to 8 KG and 2 items of baggage each up to 23 KG allowed for the flyers. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">4). Travel in the Lufthansa Airlines Business Class Flights, means in the free baggage you will get 2 items of carry-on baggage, each up to 8 kg and 2 items of baggage, each up to 32 kg. </p>
                            <p class="text-justify">5). First class passengers of Lufthansa Airlines Tickets, get 2 items of carry-on baggage, each up to 8 kg and 3 items of baggage, each up to 32 kg as the free baggage policy of the airline for the Intercontinental flights. </p>
                            <h3>2.6). You Can Book Additional Baggage in Business, First, Premium Economy and First Class: </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">If you wish to carry more baggage for your travel in the Lufthansa Air Reservations, then don’t worry about that as well because you can also book the extra baggage in the airline by paying a fee via the Lufthansa Customer Service or Lufthansa Customer Service Counter at the airport. It is your choice, how you want to proceed with that. Passengers who are traveling with the Economy Light Fare of Lufthansa can also carry one item of baggage up to 23 KG by paying a fee. </p>
                            <h4>A). How to Book Additional Baggage in Lufthansa through Web? </h4>
                            <p class="text-justify">Visit Lufthansa Official Site and click on the menu tab. Here in the first column, a section of “Book and Manage” is already given. Click on them and select ‘View and Amend Flights”. You can log in through the booking code, Lufthansa ID, and Miles and More to add additional baggage to the Lufthansa Airlines Tickets. Once the login process is complete you can add the additional baggage to the tickets through the web. </p>
                            <h3>2.7). How to Book Additional Baggage on Economy Light Fare? </h3>
                            <p class="text-justify">Choosing the economy class light fare of Lufthansa Reservations means you can save a lot on the travel ticket budget but there is also one more fact that you need to know is baggage benefits are not included in this fare class. You can also book one item of baggage per route up to 23 KG online for free. Return and outbound flights counted as one route (no matter connected is included). In this fare class, baggage charges are not refundable after the payment has been made. </p>
                            <h4>A). Choose Additional Baggage Booking Online: </h4>
                            <p class="text-justify">If you are traveling between the United States and Canada with the Economy Light Fare then the two items of baggage can also be included while paying a fee of EUR 90 or USD 100 by choosing the services of Lufthansa Customer Service Center or Counter at the airport. Flat rates per extra item of baggage are applicable in the economy class light fare as well when you want to check-in with a larger, big, heavier, and additional item of baggage. </p>
                            <h4>B). Can You Carry Sports Baggage in Lufthansa Light Fare? </h4>
                            <p class="text-justify">No, you can’t carry the sports stuff in the Light Fare of Lufthansa Flights free of cost and extra charges are applicable for the additional sports baggage. </p>
